replies.comment info:
@Chloe
1.) I agree that knitting a chart about the delays most likely stemmed from a place of boredom, or a hobby of knitting, but I disagree that it is over the top. She found a new and creative way to get her point across. If she had simply written down the numbers, I am not sure we would be discussing it now. Her eye-catching presentation of the information is why people first become intrigued by it, and then later they come to care about the problem it represents. 
2.) I like your headline and see that it could have an additional meaning that the time wasted is costing her money, as she is often late to work due to the delays. To make up for this, she made money through her knitting.
